00076 /* This function specifies the macro registers that are assumed to be killed */
00077 /* by jsr's, so returning a 1 means killed. */
00078 
00079 /* output and return params are fragile (can't be moved over function call)  */
00080 
00081 int
00082 M_tahoe_fragile_macro (int macro_value)
00083 {
00084   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00085     {
00086       switch (macro_value)
00087         {
00088           /* Integer output parameters */
00089         case L_MAC_P8:
00090         case L_MAC_P9:
00091         case L_MAC_P10:
00092         case L_MAC_P11:
00093         case L_MAC_P12:
00094         case L_MAC_P13:
00095         case L_MAC_P14:
00096         case L_MAC_P15:
00097 
00098           /* Integer return parameters */
00099         case L_MAC_P16:
00100         case L_MAC_P17:
00101         case L_MAC_P18:
00102         case L_MAC_P19:
00103 
00104           /* FP input/output parameters */
00105         case L_MAC_P20:
00106         case L_MAC_P21:
00107         case L_MAC_P22:
00108         case L_MAC_P23:
00109         case L_MAC_P24:
00110         case L_MAC_P25:
00111         case L_MAC_P26:
00112         case L_MAC_P27:
00113 
00114           /* FP return parameters */
00115         case L_MAC_P28:
00116         case L_MAC_P29:
00117         case L_MAC_P30:
00118         case L_MAC_P31:
00119 
00120         case TAHOE_MAC_AP:
00121 
00122         case TAHOE_MAC_TMPREG1:
00123         case TAHOE_MAC_TMPREG2:
00124 
00125         case TAHOE_MAC_LC:
00126         case TAHOE_MAC_EC:
00127 
00128           /* JWS -- this is a temp fix for alloca */
00129         case L_MAC_OP:
00130           return (1);
00131 
00132         default:
00133           return (0);
00134         }
00135     }
00136   else
00137     {
00138       M_assert (0, "M_tahoe_fragile_macro: illegal machine model");
00139       return (0);
00140     }
00141 }

00190 /****************************************************************************
00191  *
00192  * routine: M_tahoe_extra_pred_define_opcode()
00193  * purpose: Determine if the proc_opc opcode generates a predicate.
00194  *          Only machine specific predicate generating opcodes above and
00195  *          beyond the normal pred defines, clears, and stores need to be
00196  *          listed.
00197  * input:
00198  * output:
00199  * returns: 1 if the opcode generates a predicate.  0 otherwise
00200  * modified: Bob McGowan, 9/11/96 created
00201  *           Mark Tozer   5/30/97 added cmp4_ne_and for pred_clear
00202  * note:
00203  *       Add new opcodes to one of the 
00204  *           M_tahoe_extra_pred_define_typeX functions, too (mbt)
00205  *-------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
00206 /* 09/18/02 REK Updating to use the new TAHOEops.  The CMP4 thing is
00207  *              a little more difficult, as we will need the completer
00208  *              to figure that out.  I can't find anything that actually
00209  *              uses this function at the moment, so I'll leave that for
00210  *              later.
00211  */
00212 int
00213 M_tahoe_extra_pred_define_opcode (int proc_opc)
00214 {
00215     switch (proc_opc)
00216     {
00217     case TAHOEop_FRCPA:
00218     case TAHOEop_FRSQRTA:
00219     case TAHOEop_TBIT:
00220 #if 0
00221         /* 09/18/02 REK This needs to be fixed at some point. */
00222     case TAHOEop_CMP4_NE_AND:   /* Lop_PRED_CLEAR */
00223     case TAHOEop_CMP4_EQ_OR:    /* Lop_PRED_SET */
00224 #endif
00225         return (1);
00226     default:
00227         return (0);
00228     } /* switch */
00229 } /* M_tahoe_extra_pred_define_opcode */
00230 
00231 /************************************************************************/
00232 /* predicate-defining opcodes where both dests are pred regs (i.e. tbit)*/
00233 /************************************************************************/
00234 /* 09/18/02 REK Updating to use the new TAHOEops. */
00235 int
00236 M_tahoe_extra_pred_define_type1 (L_Oper * oper)
00237 {
00238   switch (oper->proc_opc)
00239     {
00240     case TAHOEop_TBIT:
00241         return (1);
00242 
00243     case TAHOEop_CMP:
00244         if ((oper->completers & TC_CMP_4) && \
00245             ((TC_GET_CMP_OP (oper->completers) == TC_CMP_OP_NE && \
00246               TC_GET_CMP_TYPE (oper->completers) == TC_CMP_TYPE_AND) || \
00247              (TC_GET_CMP_OP (oper->completers) == TC_CMP_OP_EQ && \
00248               TC_GET_CMP_TYPE (oper->completers) == TC_CMP_TYPE_UNC)))
00249             return (1);
00250         else
00251             return (0);
00252 
00253     default:
00254         return (0);
00255     } /* switch */
00256 } /* M_tahoe_extra_pred_define_type1 */
00257

00283 int
00284 M_tahoe_subroutine_call (int opc)
00285 {
00286 
00287   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00288     {
00289       return ((opc == Lop_JSR) || (opc == Lop_JSR_FS));
00290     }
00291   else
00292     {
00293       M_assert (0, "M_tahoe_subroutine_call:  Illegal model specified!");
00294       return (0);
00295     }
00296 }

00301 /* return 1 for macros that should be included in dataflow analysis */
00302 
00303 int
00304 M_tahoe_dataflow_macro (int id)
00305 {
00306 
00307   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00308     {
00309       switch (id)
00310         {
00311         case TAHOE_MAC_ZERO:
00312         case TAHOE_MAC_FZERO:
00313         case TAHOE_MAC_FONE:
00314         case TAHOE_MAC_PRED_TRUE:
00315         case TAHOE_MAC_TEMPLATE:
00316         case TAHOE_MAC_LABEL:
00317           return FALSE;
00318         default:
00319           return TRUE;
00320         }
00321     }
00322   else
00323     {
00324       M_assert (0, "M_tahoe_dataflow_macro: illegal machine model");
00325       return (0);
00326     }
00327 }

00475 /*
00476  * Return true (1) if the instruction is supported in the hardware of the
00477  * processor.  Return false (0) otherwise.
00478  */
00479 int
00480 M_oper_supported_in_arch_tahoe (int opc)
00481 {
00482 
00483   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00484     {
00485       switch (opc)
00486         {
00487         case Lop_MUL_ADD:
00488         case Lop_MUL_ADD_U:
00489         case Lop_MUL_SUB:
00490         case Lop_MUL_SUB_U:
00491         case Lop_MUL_SUB_REV:
00492         case Lop_MUL_SUB_REV_U:
00493         case Lop_OR_NOT:
00494         case Lop_AND_NOT:
00495         case Lop_MIN:
00496         case Lop_MAX:
00497         case Lop_ABS:
00498         case Lop_NOR:
00499         case Lop_NAND:
00500         case Lop_NXOR:
00501         case Lop_DIV:
00502         case Lop_ABS_F:
00503         case Lop_MIN_F:
00504         case Lop_MAX_F:
00505         case Lop_RCP_F:
00506           return (0);
00507 
00508         default:
00509           return (1);
00510         }
00511     }
00512   else
00513     {
00514       M_assert (0, "M_oper_supported_in_arch_tahoe: illegal machine model");
00515       return (0);
00516     }
00517 }

00520 /*
00521  * Returns the number of machine instructions required to implement the
00522  * specified oper in the best case.  It is assumed that this is for
00523  * supported instructions.  A call to M_oper_supported_in_arch should be
00524  * made for abnormal instructions.
00525  */
00526 #define zero_offset(a)   ((L_is_int_constant((a)->src[1])) && \
00527                           ((a)->src[1]->value.i == 0))
00528 #define label_base(a)    (L_is_label((a)->src[0]))
00529 
00530 int
00531 M_num_oper_required_for_tahoe (L_Oper * oper, char *name)
00532 {
00533 
00534   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00535     {
00536       switch (oper->opc)
00537         {
00538         case Lop_LD_UC:
00539         case Lop_LD_C:
00540         case Lop_LD_UC2:
00541         case Lop_LD_C2:
00542         case Lop_LD_I:
00543         case Lop_LD_UI:
00544         case Lop_LD_F:
00545         case Lop_LD_F2:
00546         case Lop_LD_Q:
00547 
00548         case Lop_ST_C:
00549         case Lop_ST_C2:
00550         case Lop_ST_I:
00551         case Lop_ST_F:
00552         case Lop_ST_F2:
00553         case Lop_ST_Q:
00554 
00555         case Lop_LD_POST_UC:
00556         case Lop_LD_POST_UC2:
00557         case Lop_LD_POST_C:
00558         case Lop_LD_POST_C2:
00559         case Lop_LD_POST_I:
00560         case Lop_LD_POST_UI:
00561         case Lop_LD_POST_Q:
00562         case Lop_LD_POST_F:
00563         case Lop_LD_POST_F2:
00564 
00565         case Lop_ST_POST_C:
00566         case Lop_ST_POST_C2:
00567         case Lop_ST_POST_I:
00568         case Lop_ST_POST_Q:
00569         case Lop_ST_POST_F:
00570         case Lop_ST_POST_F2:
00571 
00572         case Lop_LD_C_CHK:
00573         case Lop_LD_UC_CHK:
00574         case Lop_LD_C2_CHK:
00575         case Lop_LD_UC2_CHK:
00576         case Lop_LD_I_CHK:

00578         case Lop_LD_Q_CHK:
00579         case Lop_LD_F_CHK:
00580         case Lop_LD_F2_CHK:
00581 
00582           if (label_base (oper))
00583             {
00584               if (!zero_offset (oper))
00585                 return (3);
00586             }
00587           else
00588             {
00589               /* Must be register base */
00590               if (zero_offset (oper))
00591                 return (1);
00592             }
00593           return (2);
00594 
00595         case Lop_LD_PRE_UC:
00596         case Lop_LD_PRE_C:
00597         case Lop_LD_PRE_UC2:

00600         case Lop_LD_PRE_UI:
00601         case Lop_LD_PRE_Q:

00608         case Lop_ST_PRE_I:
00609         case Lop_ST_PRE_Q:
00610         case Lop_ST_PRE_F:
00611         case Lop_ST_PRE_F2:
00612 
00613           if (label_base (oper))
00614             {
00615               if (!L_is_int_constant (oper->src[1]))
00616                 return (4);
00617             }
00618           else
00619             {
00620               /* Must be register base */
00621               if (L_is_int_constant (oper->src[1]))
00622                 return (2);
00623             }
00624           return (3);
00625 
00626         case Lop_BEQ_FS:
00627         case Lop_BEQ:
00628         case Lop_BNE_FS:
00629         case Lop_BNE:
00630         case Lop_BGT_FS:

00639         case Lop_BGT_U:
00640         case Lop_BGE_U_FS:
00641         case Lop_BGE_U:
00642         case Lop_BLT_U_FS:
00643         case Lop_BLT_U:
00644         case Lop_BLE_U_FS:
00645         case Lop_BLE_U:
00646         case Lop_BEQ_F_FS:
00647         case Lop_BEQ_F:
00648         case Lop_BNE_F_FS:
00649         case Lop_BNE_F:
00650         case Lop_BGT_F_FS:
00651         case Lop_BGT_F:
00652         case Lop_BGE_F_FS:
00653         case Lop_BGE_F:
00654         case Lop_BLT_F_FS:

00659         case Lop_BEQ_F2:

00665         case Lop_BGE_F2:
00666         case Lop_BLT_F2_FS:
00667         case Lop_BLT_F2:

00669

00691         case Lop_NE_F2:

00693         case Lop_LE_F2:
00694           return (3);
00695 
00696         case Lop_MUL:

00700         case Lop_MUL_ADD:

00721       return (0);

00724 
00725 int
00726 M_num_registers_tahoe (int ctype)
00727 {
00728   if (L_is_ctype_integer_direct (ctype))
00729     {
00730       return (128);
00731     }
00732   else
00733     {
00734       switch (ctype)
00735         {
00736         case L_CTYPE_FLOAT:
00737           return (128);
00738         case L_CTYPE_DOUBLE:
00739           return (128);
00740         case L_CTYPE_PREDICATE:
00741           return (64);
00742         case L_CTYPE_BTR:
00743           return (8);
00744         default:
00745           return (0);
00746         }
00747     }
00748 }

00750 
00751 int
00752 M_is_stack_operand_tahoe (L_Operand * operand)
00753 {
00754 
00755   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00756     {
00757       if (L_is_macro (operand) &&
00758           (operand->value.mac == L_MAC_SP ||
00759            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_FP ||
00760            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_LV ||
00761            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_IP ||
00762            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_OP ||
00763            operand->value.mac == TAHOE_MAC_PSP ||
00764            operand->value.mac == TAHOE_MAC_PSPILL))
00765         {
00766           return (1);
00767         }
00768       return (0);
00769     }
00770   else
00771     {
00772       M_assert (0, "M_is_stack_operand_tahoe: illegal machine model");
00773       return (0);
00774     }
00775 }
00776 
00777 int
00778 M_is_unsafe_macro_tahoe (L_Operand * operand)
00779 {
00780 
00781   if (M_IPF_MODEL_OK (M_model))
00782     {
00783       if (!L_is_macro (operand))
00784         return (0);
00785 
00786       switch (operand->value.mac)
00787         {
00788         case TAHOE_PRED_BLK_REG: /* Register containing all the predicates   */
00789         case TAHOE_MAC_AP:
00790         case TAHOE_MAC_FPSR: /* Floating Point Status Register               */
00791         case TAHOE_MAC_ITC:  /* Interval Time Counter                        */
00792         case TAHOE_MAC_RSC:  /* Register Stack Configuration Register        */
00793         case TAHOE_MAC_BSP:  /* Backing Store Pointer For the register stack */
00794         case TAHOE_MAC_RNAT: /* RSE NAT Collection register                  */
00795         case TAHOE_MAC_UNAT: /* User NAT Collection register                 */
00796         case TAHOE_MAC_CCV:  /* Compare and Exchange Compare Value Register  */
00797         case TAHOE_MAC_KR0:  /* Kernel Register 0 */
00798         case TAHOE_MAC_KR1:  /* Kernel Register 1 */
00799         case TAHOE_MAC_KR2:  /* Kernel Register 2 */
00800         case TAHOE_MAC_KR3:  /* Kernel Register 3 */
00801 
00802         case TAHOE_MAC_LC:      /* Loop count             */
00803         case TAHOE_MAC_EC:      /* Epilogue stage counter */
00804         case TAHOE_MAC_AR_PFS:  /* Previous Frame State   */
00805 
00806         case L_MAC_SP:
00807         case L_MAC_OP:
00808 
00809           return (1);
00810         default:
00811           return (0);
00812         }
00813     }
00814   else
00815     {
00816       M_assert (0, "M_is_unsafe_macro_tahoe: illegal machine model");
00817       return (0);
00818     }
00819 }
00820 
00821 int
00822 M_operand_type_tahoe (L_Operand * operand)
00823 {
00824 
00825   /* If NULL operand pointer, then return MDES_OPERAND_NULL */
00826   if (operand == NULL)
00827     return (MDES_OPERAND_NULL);
00828 
00829   switch (operand->type)
00830     {
00831 
00832     case L_OPERAND_IMMED:
00833     case L_OPERAND_CB:
00834     case L_OPERAND_LABEL:
00835     case L_OPERAND_STRING:
00836       return (MDES_OPERAND_Lit);
00837 
00838     case L_OPERAND_MACRO:
00839     case L_OPERAND_REGISTER:
00840 
00841       if (L_is_ctype_integer (operand))
00842         {
00843           return (MDES_OPERAND_i);
00844         }
00845 
00846       else
00847         switch (operand->ctype)
00848           {
00849 
00850           case L_CTYPE_FLOAT:
00851           case L_CTYPE_DOUBLE:
00852             return (MDES_OPERAND_f);
00853           case L_CTYPE_PREDICATE:
00854             return (MDES_OPERAND_p);
00855           case L_CTYPE_BTR:
00856             return (MDES_OPERAND_btr);
00857           default:
00858             M_assert (0, "M_operand_type_tahoe: Unknown ctype");
00859             return (MDES_OPERAND_NULL);
00860           }
00861 
00862     default:
00863       M_assert (0, "M_operand_type_tahoe: Unknown type");
00864       return (MDES_OPERAND_NULL);
00865     }
00866 }

00868 
00869 int
00870 M_conflicting_operands_tahoe (L_Operand * operand,
00871                               L_Operand * conflict_array[],
00872                               int len, int prepass)
00873 {
00874   int i = 0, j;
00875 
00876   if (L_is_reg (operand))
00877     {
00878       conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
00879 
00880       if (L_is_ctype_predicate (operand) && !prepass)
00881         conflict_array[i++] =
00882           L_new_macro_operand (TAHOE_PRED_BLK_REG, L_CTYPE_LLONG,
00883                                L_PTYPE_NULL);
00884       else if (L_is_ctype_flt (operand))
00885         conflict_array[i++] =
00886           L_new_register_operand (operand->value.r,
00887                                   L_CTYPE_DOUBLE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00888       else if (L_is_ctype_dbl (operand))
00889         conflict_array[i++] =
00890           L_new_register_operand (operand->value.r,
00891                                   L_CTYPE_FLOAT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00892     }
00893   else if (L_is_macro (operand))
00894     {
00895       switch (operand->value.mac)
00896         {
00897         case L_MAC_SP:
00898         case L_MAC_FP:
00899         case L_MAC_SAFE_MEM:
00900         case L_MAC_LV:
00901         case L_MAC_OP:
00902         case L_MAC_IP:
00903           conflict_array[i++] =
00904             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_SP, L_CTYPE_LLONG, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00905           conflict_array[i++] =
00906             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_FP, L_CTYPE_LLONG, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00907           conflict_array[i++] =
00908             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_SAFE_MEM, L_CTYPE_LLONG, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00909           conflict_array[i++] =
00910             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_LV, L_CTYPE_LLONG, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00911           conflict_array[i++] =
00912             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_OP, L_CTYPE_LLONG, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00913           conflict_array[i++] =
00914             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_IP, L_CTYPE_LLONG, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00915           break;
00916 
00917         case TAHOE_PRED_BLK_REG:
00918           conflict_array[i++] =
00919             L_new_macro_operand (TAHOE_PRED_BLK_REG, L_CTYPE_LLONG,
00920                                  L_PTYPE_NULL);
00921           for (j = 1; j <= 63; j++)
00922             {
00923               conflict_array[i++] =
00924                 L_new_register_operand (TAHOE_PRED_REG_BASE + j,
00925                                         L_CTYPE_PREDICATE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00926             }
00927           break;
00928 
00929           /* Floating-point parameter regs doubled-up on tahoe */
00930         case L_MAC_P20:
00931         case L_MAC_P21:
00932         case L_MAC_P22:
00933         case L_MAC_P23:
00934         case L_MAC_P24:
00935         case L_MAC_P25:
00936         case L_MAC_P26:
00937         case L_MAC_P27:
00938           conflict_array[i++] =
00939             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac,
00940                                  L_CTYPE_FLOAT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00941           conflict_array[i++] =
00942             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac,
00943                                  L_CTYPE_DOUBLE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00944           conflict_array[i++] =
00945             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac + 8,
00946                                  L_CTYPE_FLOAT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00947           conflict_array[i++] =
00948             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac + 8,
00949                                  L_CTYPE_DOUBLE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00950           break;
00951         case L_MAC_P28:
00952         case L_MAC_P29:
00953         case L_MAC_P30:
00954         case L_MAC_P31:
00955         case L_MAC_P32:
00956         case L_MAC_P33:
00957         case L_MAC_P34:
00958         case L_MAC_P35:
00959           conflict_array[i++] =
00960             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac,
00961                                  L_CTYPE_FLOAT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00962           conflict_array[i++] =
00963             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac,
00964                                  L_CTYPE_DOUBLE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00965           conflict_array[i++] =
00966             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac - 8,
00967                                  L_CTYPE_FLOAT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00968           conflict_array[i++] =
00969             L_new_macro_operand (operand->value.mac - 8,
00970                                  L_CTYPE_DOUBLE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00971           break;
00972 
00973         case TAHOE_MAC_ZERO:
00974         case TAHOE_MAC_FZERO:
00975         case TAHOE_MAC_FONE:
00976         case TAHOE_MAC_PRED_TRUE:
00977           break;
00978 
00979         default:
00980           conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
00981         }
00982     }
00983   M_assert (i <= len, "Ltahoe_conflicting_operands: too many conflicts!");
00984   return (i);
00985 }

01390 /****************************************************************************
01391  *
01392  * routine: M_cannot_predicate_tahoe
01393  * purpose: returns true if the oper cannot be predicated
01394  * input:
01395  * output:
01396  * returns:
01397  * modified: Created JEP 1/29/98
01398  * note:
01399     Pred clear instructions are assumed to have no qualifying 
01400     predicate by predicate flow analysis.  
01401  *-------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
01402 
01403 int
01404 M_cannot_predicate_tahoe (L_Oper * oper)
01405 {
01406 
01407   switch (oper->opc)
01408     {
01409 
01410     case Lop_PRED_CLEAR:
01411     case Lop_PRED_SET:
01412       return (1);
01413 
01414     default:
01415       return (0);
01416     }
01417 }
01418 
01419 void
01420 M_get_memory_operands_tahoe (int *first, int *number, int proc_opc)
01421 {
01422   /*
01423    * After annotation, tahoe memory ops have no offset.
01424    *
01425    * This is grotesque, but it allows the TAHOE model to be used
01426    * before and after annotation.
01427    */
01428 
01429   if (proc_opc <= Lop_LAST_OP)
01430     {
01431       *first = 0;
01432       *number = 2;
01433     }
01434   else
01435     {
01436       *first = 0;
01437       *number = 1;
01438     }
01439 }
